olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 bag salad leaves
1 bag herbs
1 packet ponzu sauce
1 tsp sesame oil
1 drizzle rice wine vinegar
1 packet Carrot Noodles
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet Chilli Jam
¼ cup water
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet Crushed Peanuts

• Finely chop garlic. Roughly chop salad leaves. Thinly slice herbs.
• In a large bowl, combine ponzu sauce, sesame oil and a drizzle of rice wine
vinegar. Add carrot noodles and toss to combine. Season with pepper and
set aside.

• In a medium bowl, combine beef mince, sweet soy seasoning
and garlic.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of mixture into small meatballs
(4-5 meatballs per person). Transfer to a plate.

• In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of olive oil over medium-high
heat. Cook meatballs, turning, until browned and cooked through,
8-10 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove pan from heat, then add chilli jam and the water and toss to coat
meatballs. Season to taste.

TIP: Add a splash more water if the glaze looks too thick.

• Add shredded cabbage mix and salad leaves to carrot noodles and toss
to combine.
• Divide carrot noodle salad between bowls.
• Top with chilli jam-glazed beef meatballs. Spoon any remaining glaze over
the meatballs and carrot noodles.
• Dollop over mayonnaise. Sprinkle with crushed peanuts and herbs
to serve.